.TH "usb_hcd_alloc_bandwidth" 9 "usb_hcd_alloc_bandwidth" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_hcd_alloc_bandwidth \- check whether a new bandwidth setting exceeds the bus bandwidth
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" usb_hcd_alloc_bandwidth
.BI "(struct usb_device *udev "  ","
.BI "struct usb_host_config *new_config "  ","
.BI "struct usb_host_interface *cur_alt "  ","
.BI "struct usb_host_interface *new_alt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "udev" 12
target \fIusb_device\fP
.IP "new_config" 12
new configuration to install
.IP "cur_alt" 12
the current alternate interface setting
.IP "new_alt" 12
alternate interface setting that is being installed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
To change configurations, pass in the new configuration in new_config,
and pass NULL for cur_alt and new_alt.

To reset a device's configuration (put the device in the ADDRESSED state),
pass in NULL for new_config, cur_alt, and new_alt.

To change alternate interface settings, pass in NULL for new_config,
pass in the current alternate interface setting in cur_alt,
and pass in the new alternate interface setting in new_alt.
.SH "RETURN"
An error if the requested bandwidth change exceeds the
bus bandwidth or host controller internal resources.
